<font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="4" color="#990000"><b>What else to read</b></font><p>
<font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">For an overview of Iranian history up to recent years, Nikki Keddie's <i><a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/redirect.html?ie=UTF8&location=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FModern-Iran-Results-Revolution-Updated%2Fdp%2F0300121059%2Fsr%3D8-1%2Fqid%3D1159828112%2Fref%3Dpd%5Fbbs%5F1%3Fie%3DUTF8%26s%3Dbooks&tag=socialistwork-20&linkCode=ur2&camp=1789&creative=9325" target="_blank">Modern Iran: Roots and Results of Revolution</a> </i>is the best place to start. For a detailed account of the clash between conservatives and reformers, see Mehdi Moslem's <i><a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/redirect.html?ie=UTF8&location=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FFactional-Politics-Post-Khomeini-Intellectual-Political%2Fdp%2F0815629788%2Fsr%3D1-1%2Fqid%3D1159828157%2Fref%3Dsr%5F1%5F1%3Fie%3DUTF8%26s%3Dbooks&tag=socialistwork-20&linkCode=ur2&camp=1789&creative=9325" target="_blank">Factional Politics in Post-Khomeini Iran</a> </i>and <i><a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/redirect.html?ie=UTF8&location=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FDemocracy-Iran-History-Quest-Liberty%2Fdp%2F0195189671%2Fsr%3D1-1%2Fqid%3D1159828185%2Fref%3Dsr%5F1%5F1%3Fie%3DUTF8%26s%3Dbooks&tag=socialistwork-20&linkCode=ur2&camp=1789&creative=9325" target="_blank">Democracy in Iran: History and the Quest for Liberty</a> </i>by Ali Gheissari and Vali Nasr. An overview of Iran's important left can be found in <i><a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/redirect.html?ie=UTF8&location=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FReformers-Revolutionaries-Routledgecurzon-Persian-Studies%2Fdp%2F0415331285%2Fref%3Dsr%5F11%5F1%3Fie%3DUTF8&tag=socialistwork-20&linkCode=ur2&camp=1789&creative=9325" target="_blank">Reformers and Revolutionaries in Modern Iran</a>, </i>edited by Stephanie Cronin.<p>
